      "id": "91e8b84e_31560238",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "message": "- please beautify all (old and new) json files\n- I am not so sure if the cmHandeId is the best way to choose a module(set) It is not very readably ie. you cannot tell from the names easily which module(set) will be used :-(\n\nCan you instead do somethign with a prefix ie. split cmHnaldeId on a token (- or _ or similar) can then use the prefix(type) to (build) a filename for the response (with a backup default option)\n\nPseudo code:\n\ne.g. cmHandleId = 'bookStore-123'\n\ndefaultNodeType = 'ietfYang'\nnodeType = cmHandleId .split('-')[0]\nresponseFileName = nodeType+'ModuleResponse.json'\nif !file(responseFileName).exists() {\n  responseFileName = defaultNodeType +'ModuleResponse.json'\n}\n\netc.\n\nThis mean you wil have to change the Existing CIST (and performance) Test as well to use the new names but I think it will improve the understanding of the tests...\nAnd better control of what modules are used where",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2024-01-05 10:26:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
